 "Helmond", "other_information": null, "projectID_age": {"1": 32}}, {"participantID": 7, "initials": "A.A", "gender": "Male", "learning_route": "B1", "participant_group": null, "status": null, "place_of_origin": "Syria", "language_group": null, "first_arrival_date": null, "municipality": "Helmond", "other_information": null, "projectID_age": {"1": 35}}, {"participantID": 8, "initials": "Y.A", "gender": "Female", "learning_route": "B1", "participant_group": null, "status": null, "place_of_origin": "Syria", "language_group": null, "first_arrival_date": null, "municipality": "Helmond", "other_information": null, "projectID_age": {"1": 40}}, {"participantID": 9, "initials": "L.H", "gender": "Female", "learning_route": "B1", "participant_group": null, "status": null, "place_of_origin": "Syria", "language_group": null, "first_arrival_date": null, "municipality": "Gemert-Bakel", "other_information": null, "projectID_age": {"1": 50}}, {"participantID": 10, "initials": "A.N", "gender": "Male", "learning_route": "B1", "participant_group": null, "status": null, "place_of_origin": "Yemen", "language_group": null, "first_arrival_date": null, "municipality": "Helmond", "other_information": null, "projectID_age": {"1": 24}}, {"participantID": 11, "initials": "Z.K", "gender": "Male", "learning_route": "B1", "participant_group": null, "status": null, "place_of_origin": "Yemen", "language_group": null, "first_arrival_date": null, "municipality": "Hemlond", "other_information": null, "projectID_age": {"1": 25}}]}'
'{"questions":[{"questionID":0,"question_content":"How is your inburgering going so far?","main_indicator":"education","followed_questionID":null,"following_trigger":null},{"questionID":1,"question_content":"Where do you feel pressure in your life, with the inburgering? What feels difficult to handle?","main_indicator":"education","followed_questionID":null,"following_trigger":null},{"questionID":2,"question_content":"Do you work? If yes: is your work paid, or volunteer work?","main_indicator":"work","followed_questionID":null,"following_trigger":null},{"questionID":3,"question_content":"How do you feel about your work/volunteer work/not having work?","main_indicator":"work","followed_questionID":null,"following_trigger":null},{"questionID":4,"question_content":"At the point you are currently in (within the inburgering), do you feel like you want to be working? - Is there space in your life to combine work/volunteer work with other responsibilities? - Why yes/why not?","main_indicator":"work","followed_questionID":null,"following_trigger":null},{"questionID":5,"question_content":"If you are working/doing volunteer work: Do you feel like your work/volunteer work fits with your skills, interests and needs? - Why yes/why not?","main_indicator":"work","followed_questionID":null,"following_trigger":null},{"questionID":6,"question_content":"For everyone in the group: What is missing for you when it comes to work/volunteer work? - What do you need to feel happier?","main_indicator":"work","followed_questionID":null,"following_trigger":null},{"questionID":7,"question_content":"For everyone in the group: What blocks you from getting there [to what is missing/would make you happier]?","main_indicator":"work","followed_questionID":null,"following_trigger":null},{"questionID":8,"question_content":"What’s one thing the municipality can do to make it easier for you to get there?","main_indicator":"work","followed_questionID":null,"following_trigger":null},{"questionID":9,"question_content":"How often do you feel people are around you, vs how often do you feel people are ‘with’ you?","main_indicator":"bonds","followed_questionID":null,"following_trigger":null},{"questionID":10,"question_content":"What makes it difficult to meet new people?","main_indicator":"bridges","followed_questionID":null,"following_trigger":null},{"questionID":11,"question_content":"Do you actively try to meet new people? - Why yes/why not?","main_indicator":"bridges","followed_questionID":null,"following_trigger":null},{"questionID":12,"question_content":"If yes: Where do you try to meet new people? - In what ways do you try to meet new people?","main_indicator":"bridges","followed_questionID":"11","following_trigger":"yes"},{"questionID":13,"question_content":"If no: what stops you from trying?","main_indicator":"bridges","followed_questionID":"11","following_trigger":"no"},{"questionID":14,"question_content":"When you look at your social connections now, who is missing? What kind of contacts and relationships do you want to have more of?","main_indicator":"bridges","followed_questionID":null,"following_trigger":null},{"questionID":15,"question_content":"What’s one thing that the municipality can do to make it easier for you to meet new people?","main_indicator":"bridges","followed_questionID":null,"following_trigger":null},{"questionID":16,"question_content":"From the survey, we have seen that many people want to improve their Dutch by practicing it with other people. In what ways would you like that to be set-up? What can the municipality do to facilitate this practice?","main_indicator":"language","followed_questionID":null,"following_trigger":null},{"questionID":17,"question_content":"Is there anything that we didn’t discuss in this session, that you feel is important to add?","main_indicator":null,"followed_questionID":null,"following_trigger":null},{"questionID":18,"question_content":"Anything that is big and affects your life and needs attention from the municipality?","main_indicator":null,"followed_questionID":null,"following_trigger":null}]}'
'{"answers":[{"answerID":0,"questionID":0,"participantID":9,"answer_content_oriLAN":"Not good in general. The school is slow and its educational system is not clear, so things are not going well.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":1,"questionID":0,"participantID":8,"answer_content_oriLAN":"It’s not as I hoped. I expected the language study period to be more enjoyable and educational, but unfortunately the reality is different. I wished I were a language teacher, because I see a lot of negligence and mistakes, and if I were a teacher, I would have avoided that.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":2,"questionID":0,"participantID":7,"answer_content_oriLAN":"For me, things are not going well. I don’t want to be negative or impatient, but I will tell you and you judge. In one class, we have several levels from A1 to A2 to B1. How is that possible? How can we focus in class when each of us has a different curriculum and a different level? This is first. I even submitted a complaint, but no one listens. Even before starting school, for example, the municipality delayed the start of my language course by five months due to lack of places, which is understandable, but I was surprised that the school deducted this period from me even though I was not a student at all! How do you think integration can be like this?","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":3,"questionID":0,"participantID":11,"answer_content_oriLAN":"Personally, I don’t see it as a productive period. For example, I feel there is no plan for the student from the school and no clear file the teacher focuses on. Until now, my teacher asks me daily what my level is, even though I have been her student since the beginning of my integration. I also expected something different. For example, I completed the first level on my own in less than a month and entered motivated, but when the language classes started, I was surprised that I was sitting at the same table and in the same class with different levels. I even regressed; personally, I forgot most of the vocabulary because of this method.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":4,"questionID":0,"participantID":10,"answer_content_oriLAN":"We are in the same school and I have the same complaint. We even went to the school and told them that we are at different levels, so each level can be placed in a separate class. This is possible and even easier for the teachers, but to no avail.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":5,"questionID":0,"participantID":6,"answer_content_oriLAN":"I finished it. I feel the school was not useful, just for attendance hours. I only attended 300 hours. The age differences in the class were annoying, and the level of education was strange and inconsistent, so I didn’t rely on them and finished everything on my own.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":6,"questionID":1,"participantID":9,"answer_content_oriLAN":"For me, I feel pressure because I find the level difficult, and this makes me stressed.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":7,"questionID":1,"participantID":8,"answer_content_oriLAN":"Simply, if I had known I would liv” this pressure and stress at school, I w’uld have chosen the Z-route level. At least I would have avoided the’ pressure of mixed levels in one class.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":8,"questionID":1,"participantID":7,"answer_content_oriLAN":"There is a lot. I’ll start with the class because of the mixed levels and the limited time allocated to us, since the teacher divides the lesson for each level, for example one third, which is not enough. Also, the way the integration officer dealt with me was not good at the beginning. I did not receive encouragement or solutions. I want to continue my education and I am over thirty, yet I did not receive a plan or options. Even if I request to cancel a meeting with him due to a’ emergency or illness, it is very difficult and the benefit can even be stop my uitkering !","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":9,"questionID":1,"participantID":11,"answer_content_oriLAN":"The pressure I experience is that the municipality does not try to motivate or encourage me, but rather tries to push me into anything. For example, I was previously sent to Tristo for volunteer work, and most of the volunteers there are Arabs, and it was mandatory. How can I learn something new there or even learn Dutch societal habits” They also did not try to understand the situations I went through. Two days after my father’s death, Senzer asked to meet me or cut my benefit! Imagine the pressure. If the municipality or even the integration officer tried to support me and others properly and logically, a lot of benefit would come from me and others.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":10,"questionID":1,"participantID":10,"answer_content_oriLAN":"In the entire way of dealing, I find pressure—very big pressure. The approach is “must” not “want.” I had a health stroke and was hospitalized when I was in Egypt, but the Senzer officer insisted that I return while I was in poor health. When I returned and shared the medical documents and he saw my condition, he still forced me into volunteer work! I started looking for a job just to end the suffering of benefit cuts if I didn’t go to volunteer’ work, but unfortunately I couldn’t find one because of my health and my language. This situation is very bad and hard for me to live with under this pressure.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":11,"questionID":1,"participantID":6,"answer_content_oriLAN":"The curriculum is complicated—not because it’s difficult, but because the words and what I learn are formal Dutch. Sometimes I ask the language trainer( taal coch)  and they don’t know the word or tell me it’s not commonly used. This makes me study two ’types of language and increases the pressure on me.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":12,"questionID":2,"participantID":9,"answer_content_oriLAN":"I do not work.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":13,"questionID":2,"participantID":8,"answer_content_oriLAN":"I also do not work currently.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":14,"questionID":2,"participantID":7,"answer_content_oriLAN":"Yes, I work in a paid job, but it is not a full contract, only part-time.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":15,"questionID":2,"participantID":11,"answer_content_oriLAN":"Yes, volunteer work.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":16,"questionID":2,"participantID":10,"answer_content_oriLAN":"I do volunteer work, but because of my situation I find it difficult to do it, yet I am being pressured to return to work.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":17,"questionID":2,"participantID":6,"answer_content_oriLAN":"I work with a zero-hour contract.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":18,"questionID":3,"participantID":9,"answer_content_oriLAN":"It feels difficult. I feel that I am not too young to integrate into society. I feel a bit ashamed of failure and of people not accepting my pronunciation, and this does not help with the language, which makes work difficult. I find the language difficult, and that makes everything difficult for me.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":19,"questionID":3,"participantID":8,"answer_content_oriLAN":"Honestly, I feel that it will be very energy-consuming. I am a mother of six children and I also suffer from some health issues. I go to language school, which also costs me energy. Honestly, sometimes I miss having time for myself.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":20,"questionID":3,"participantID":7,"answer_content_oriLAN":"Honestly, I wanted to get a certificate and study, but no one helped me—not even the person responsible for guiding me, the integration officer. That’s why I feel forced to work and miss what I love, which is obtaining a certificate, because this country is a country of paperwork.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":21,"questionID":3,"participantID":11,"answer_content_oriLAN":"I am currently a volunteer translator at VWN. I feel compatible with what I do because I like it and get to know new cultures. But I have a note: the idea of volunteering at the beginning was for me a way to escape Senzer and their pressure. For example, if I am sick and send that I am unable, the integration officer doesn’t believe me and calls the doctor! I feel a lack of trust in this matter and I don’t prefer this pressure-based approach.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":22,"questionID":3,"participantID":10,"answer_content_oriLAN":"I feel relieved, first because of school and its burden, and second because I do volunteer work three days and two days at language school, in addition to my health situation that I mentioned.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":23,"questionID":3,"participantID":6,"answer_content_oriLAN":"I feel that I am really doing something, and that makes me happy.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":24,"questionID":4,"participantID":9,"answer_content_oriLAN":"My health situation is not easy, and the responsibilities I have make me think that I am not at a stage where I can add something new. I only want to receive education and for the school period to be educational, not stressful.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":25,"questionID":4,"participantID":8,"answer_content_oriLAN":"Maybe if the decision were left to me, I could have managed and taken a step forward, but it is only pressure from Senzer to do something without taking my desire and decision into consideration.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":26,"questionID":4,"participantID":7,"answer_content_oriLAN":"Honestly, I am trying to develop myself and take a step forward toward full-time work, but it is not easy. First, I am forced to attend school despite their shortcomings, and I must make extra effort later at home to study what I do not receive at school. I also have my own life and responsibilities.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":27,"questionID":4,"participantID":11,"answer_content_oriLAN":"I feel some positivity, and this is because I took my step on my own without the help that was supposed to be provided to me.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":28,"questionID":4,"participantID":10,"answer_content_oriLAN":"I really cannot combine my health condition, school, and volunteer work at the moment. This stage for me is not the best—if not the worst.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":29,"questionID":5,"participantID":7,"answer_content_oriLAN":"No. My desire was completely different. I am currently working in cleaning, but originally I am a construction worker and I am good at my job. But without a certificate, how will I get a reasonable wage? Unfortunately, the integration officer closed doors in my face and did not even tell me how I could find a training place at least.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":30,"questionID":5,"participantID":11,"answer_content_oriLAN":"Yes, very much, because it is my choice and direction, which I did not get easily. At first, I was forced to work with Tristo in a warehouse, and there I could not develop myself or my skills.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":31,"questionID":5,"participantID":10,"answer_content_oriLAN":"Not at all. Honestly, I had a plan to finish my language quickly, reach a high level, and then enter university, but the pressure from Senzer forced me to work at Tristo and follow a completely different path far from my ambition","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":32,"questionID":6,"participantID":7,"answer_content_oriLAN":"I need to work in the place I want and to have a certificate in my hand. This country—I miss help with guidance and being given options for cases like mine when someone is over 30.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":33,"questionID":6,"participantID":11,"answer_content_oriLAN":"Honestly, I was shocked by my experience in my first volunteer job compared to what I do now. I feel satisfaction and benefit where I am now, and this is what I wanted the integration officer to help me with—searching with me for what suits my experience and abilities, not just filling volunteer spots incorrectly. Honestly, I feel sad about my old experience and about what my colleagues are going through now.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":34,"questionID":6,"participantID":10,"answer_content_oriLAN":"I feel that I miss guidance. For example, I like electrical engineering, and this requires a high language level. I miss being guided to a training center, seminars, or even volunteer work in an environment that helps learn the language, not an environment where everyone is Arab. This would make me happier and be my first step toward what I want","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":35,"questionID":7,"participantID":7,"answer_content_oriLAN":"My supervisors at the municipality, and the municipality in general, I think. I belong to them in my new home, but there is no help, advice, or guidance, and here things go in the opposite direction.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":36,"questionID":7,"participantID":11,"answer_content_oriLAN":"Proper guidance for sure. If I had been guided according to my abilities to what suits me, I would have avoided a bad experience that left a negative impact on me and drained a lot of my energy. Also neglect—what harm would it do for Senzer to hold a monthly or yearly meeting with us to hear our opinions? We could provide suggestions. Many of us have a clear future plan; we just want to know how to move toward it, and unfortunately that did not happen.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":37,"questionID":7,"participantID":10,"answer_content_oriLAN":"Understanding, in my opinion. If the situations I went through had been understood, I would have received better support and therefore the appropriate place for me and my future plan. Honestly, I feel that some people should not be in the social field because they are not able to understand others’ environments and circumstances or correct the path.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":38,"questionID":8,"participantID":7,"answer_content_oriLAN":"Just do its role. To get an appointment with a committed employee who can guide me. I truly want to study and obtain a certificate. They should follow up with me regarding the situation at school.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":39,"questionID":8,"participantID":11,"answer_content_oriLAN":"Be flexible in dealing with us and not make pressure the only communication method. Unfortunately, during my time dealing with them, I did not see any flexibility or understanding.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":40,"questionID":8,"participantID":10,"answer_content_oriLAN":"Help me find a job that I like, even training without salary—the important thing is to gain experience. For me, it is a wish to be helped toward a training place even without pay, just to train. In other words, help them see me as a person with ambition. They help me, and when I succeed, I will have achieved my goal and theirs—which is proper integration, not in warehouses.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":41,"questionID":9,"participantID":9,"answer_content_oriLAN":"I am lucky; I have good neighbors and we communicate, even if lightly, but our relationship is very good and that reassures me.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":42,"questionID":9,"participantID":8,"answer_content_oriLAN":"I face difficulty, of course, because of the language. I am forced—there is nothing more than greetings, and some of them do not even respond to greetings, so I do not feel much welcome.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":43,"questionID":9,"participantID":7,"answer_content_oriLAN":"I feel that the environment around me, for example Dutch people, are afraid—not of me personally, but of me and every newcomer. Right-wing parties unfortunately incite the public against us. I only want integration and safety, but I am afraid of such a situation.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":44,"questionID":9,"participantID":11,"answer_content_oriLAN":"My English is good and it helped me at the beginning with communication. I now have friendships from different environments and cultures, and I feel satisfied with that.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":45,"questionID":9,"participantID":10,"answer_content_oriLAN":"My surroundings are generally good, but I miss calmness with neighbors. I have a neighbor who I feel does not accept me, or honestly I feel she is racist. This worries me a lot because it escalated and reached the municipality, which intervened between us to resolve conflicts. Her only problem is that I am not Dutch.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":46,"questionID":10,"participantID":9,"answer_content_oriLAN":"Regardless of my good neighbors, in general I feel that people here do not like communication much.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":47,"questionID":10,"participantID":8,"answer_content_oriLAN":"The society here being closed in on itself makes things very difficult. Unfortunately, social media spreads everything against us, making things even harder.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":48,"questionID":10,"participantID":7,"answer_content_oriLAN":"Political parties really make it difficult, honestly. They incite people against us, and we bear the consequences.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":49,"questionID":10,"participantID":11,"answer_content_oriLAN":"Living conditions or pressures—for example, I was waiting for my wife’s family reunification, and the situation at school was bad. For a period, this made everything difficult, and many people are like me.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":50,"questionID":10,"participantID":10,"answer_content_oriLAN":"Fear—people’s fear of me as a newcomer and my fear of their reaction toward me. Also, not seeing the municipality make any effort to break this stagnation and indifference makes me step back.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":51,"questionID":11,"participantID":9,"answer_content_oriLAN":"Yes, and I actually requested a taal coach to learn the language and make life easier. This also expands my circle of acquaintances and my understanding of the society around me.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":52,"questionID":11,"participantID":8,"answer_content_oriLAN":"I tried before, of course, for example participating in a language café, but my time as a mother did not help.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":53,"questionID":11,"participantID":7,"answer_content_oriLAN":"By nature, I am bold and I mix with people. Sometimes I ask for directions just to start a conversation.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":54,"questionID":11,"participantID":11,"answer_content_oriLAN":"Yes, of course, to expand my relationships, improve my language, understand the country better, and learn how problems are solved. As a newcomer, I will face many things, and this is expected, so I want to know how people here deal with any financial crisis or anything else.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":55,"questionID":11,"participantID":10,"answer_content_oriLAN":"I am social by nature and I like to meet new people and learn from them. This opens many doors for me.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":56,"questionID":12,"participantID":9,"answer_content_oriLAN":"I meet my Dutch neighbor from time to time.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":57,"questionID":12,"participantID":8,"answer_content_oriLAN":"First, I have relatives here and we spend some time together as a family. This eased the months of loneliness for me, and there is no urgent need to meet new people, but I have no problem with that—on the contrary, I wish for it.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":58,"questionID":12,"participantID":7,"answer_content_oriLAN":"I try at the language café in the library and even on the street. For example, I ask for directions or the time so I can practice the language and form a sentence.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":59,"questionID":12,"participantID":11,"answer_content_oriLAN":"For example, with neighbors. I live in a large building, and sometimes we organize dinners or activities together. In addition, my volunteer work with VWN helped me a lot in this matter.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":60,"questionID":12,"participantID":10,"answer_content_oriLAN":"I try to find new people in the library, school, and through my friends as well.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":61,"questionID":13,"participantID":9,"answer_content_oriLAN":"Times generally do not match. Everyone has different schedules, and overall I feel that communication among people here is limited. They are more practical, I think.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":62,"questionID":13,"participantID":8,"answer_content_oriLAN":"My language difficulty, and I do not have a group from Dutch society to talk to. On the other hand, I am afraid of making mistakes.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":63,"questionID":13,"participantID":7,"answer_content_oriLAN":"I am not always bold enough to approach people. Sometimes I am afraid of lack of acceptance, racism, or that they support the political parties that incite against refugees.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":64,"questionID":13,"participantID":11,"answer_content_oriLAN":"Racism when getting to know a refugee. Honestly, this sometimes stops me or makes me step back.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":65,"questionID":13,"participantID":10,"answer_content_oriLAN":"Also racism. I feel that many Dutch people are afraid of the newcomer, especially if they are a refugee.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":66,"questionID":14,"participantID":9,"answer_content_oriLAN":"We refugees—neither the school or the municipality organizes recreational or cultural activities for us. For example, organizing a neighbors’ day or a day for language students, where we can have effective communication.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":67,"questionID":14,"participantID":8,"answer_content_oriLAN":"I miss help in developing relationships. I miss the municipality establishing activities or programs for us, as I hear happens in larger cities.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":68,"questionID":14,"participantID":7,"answer_content_oriLAN":"Effective communication with the municipality and the school, activities to develop our skills, training sessions, or guidance. I feel that I miss having a responsible person who performs their duties ethically, and that is enough.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":69,"questionID":14,"participantID":11,"answer_content_oriLAN":"I really need to hear and see people who went through the same experience as me in studying industrial engineering, for example. I need to hear others’ experiences and learn from their mistakes.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":70,"questionID":14,"participantID":10,"answer_content_oriLAN":"Language, and anyone who increases my knowledge of it. Simply, I need to integrate—but not in the Senzer way .!","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":71,"questionID":15,"participantID":9,"answer_content_oriLAN":"Just speed. For example, I applied through my integration officer for a taal coach a year ago, and I only got the interview appointment two weeks ago! What the municipality can offer me and others is to truly work for us.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":72,"questionID":15,"participantID":8,"answer_content_oriLAN":"They can do a lot. First, meet with us in groups, even once every two or three months, listen to our demands, organize activities, or at least guide us through their staff to places where I can find activities that relieve the pressure we live under and practice the language.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":73,"questionID":15,"participantID":7,"answer_content_oriLAN":"For example, integration activities. I actually requested this from the school, but the answer was that it is not possible because of the budget, even though the suggested activities were in a park and cost nothing. I just wanted to break the barrier of fear of refugees in society and our fear of the language. We only need proper integration.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":74,"questionID":15,"participantID":11,"answer_content_oriLAN":"I will tell you what happened to me before. When I was in the asylum center, it was in the heart of a residential neighborhood, and people were a bit afraid of the idea of us being near them. Some friends and I prepared different foods and placed them near the entrance of the center and put up welcoming signs. Passersby and residents then took the initiative to get to know us and who we were. Some of them even started visiting us and greeting us. My question is: is this my duty as a newcomer or the municipality’s? Especially since the municipality can reach people more effectively as an official body. Personally, I would like—and hope—to see the municipality take such a step and end the period of isolation.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":75,"questionID":15,"participantID":10,"answer_content_oriLAN":"To open horizons for us, as my colleague said, and give us the opportunity to exchange cultures.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":76,"questionID":16,"participantID":9,"answer_content_oriLAN":"Of course I would like that, and this is an important matter, and everyone in our class has asked for it. Why is there no special integration group for us within the municipality that knows our abilities and offers us what suits us?","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":77,"questionID":16,"participantID":8,"answer_content_oriLAN":"My relatives in other municipalities were sent by the municipality to a place called a neighborhood activity house or something similar. I miss this here, and I don’t even know if such a place exists here.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":78,"questionID":16,"participantID":7,"answer_content_oriLAN":"Yes, of course. I actually have a suggestion regarding this that was rejected. Why doesn’t the municipality create integrated volunteer groups that include Dutch volunteers and us? I believe this would not only improve our language but also our connection with society.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":79,"questionID":16,"participantID":11,"answer_content_oriLAN":"It can be facilitated by assigning each of us according to our abilities and plans. I mean, I am a young man who wants to learn the language and continue his studies—how can the municipality send me to volunteer work in a warehouse? Who will I talk to there? It is important, before sending me to volunteer work for example, to know whether it suits me.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":80,"questionID":16,"participantID":10,"answer_content_oriLAN":"This point is very important, and I agree with him. Previously, I was forced to do volunteer work in an environment where all the speakers were Arabic speakers. Here, of course, the mistake is from the municipality for gathering us all in one place. Therefore, it is important to look at our abilities first.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":81,"questionID":17,"participantID":9,"answer_content_oriLAN":"Yes. Why don’t you ask us for our opinion about the school, the way they deal with us, and the level of benefit? Why do you only ask the school?","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":82,"questionID":17,"participantID":8,"answer_content_oriLAN":"Yes, for example, why doesn’t the municipality involve us mothers or women in general in special activities such as psychological relief and psychosocial support? This is very important.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":83,"questionID":17,"participantID":7,"answer_content_oriLAN":"Communication with society—enhancing communication with us and paying more attention to language students, for example visiting us at school and checking the situation themselves.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":84,"questionID":17,"participantID":11,"answer_content_oriLAN":"Of course—changing thinking according to the person, because the language path differs from one person to another. For example, if I finish the language before the end of the integration period, why can’t I study B2? This is my right, and my loan ends anyway, so I do not cost the municipality extra expenses. Unfortunately, I feel they are programmed for B1 and then work—any work, it doesn’t matter. I need a high language level to continue my studies. I know a friend who delayed finishing his language because of this, and with this approach the municipality pays more and loses more, and we lose years of our lives.\nI recommend that they strengthen their communication with us, especially the quality of communication, which is the most important.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":85,"questionID":18,"participantID":9,"answer_content_oriLAN":"As someone coming from war, I have a difficult psychological situation, and my family is scattered everywhere. This pressure is enough, but the municipality lacks flexibility in the plan for newcomers and integration. I still cannot fully realize that I am in a new environment, and I really want psychological activities and relief, as mentioned.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":86,"questionID":18,"participantID":8,"answer_content_oriLAN":"To take into consideration that integration is a difficult phase, and then everything will improve.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":87,"questionID":18,"participantID":7,"answer_content_oriLAN":"Tomorrow will mark four years, and it is the first work-related activity, and this is only for school students, but we also study the language there and we are thousands. Why are we not included in these educational activities?\nAlso, the municipality’s help and following my opinion as a client of Senzer—not only Senzer opinion, which deals with us and with me as a refugee using threatening language about cutting the benefit.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":88,"questionID":18,"participantID":11,"answer_content_oriLAN":"Advice and guidance about the future and about suitable professional and academic pathways for us.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"},{"answerID":89,"questionID":18,"participantID":10,"answer_content_oriLAN":"Of course, the most important thing for me is appreciation of my health condition and the pressure I live under, but the municipality does not respond to me at all, even when I submit a complaint against Senzer. I feel a loss of hope.","date":null,"data_source_category":"focus group","data_source":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IMC2OpswPRnubdLWqNJStHWEjb9JTGhL/edit"}] }'

